Read the following text to answer number 7-9!

How to Make Cemplon

Tools and ingredients:

  • Cassava
  • grated coconut
  • brown sugar
  • oil
  • a teaspoon of salt
  • a knife
  • a grater
  • a frying pan

The steps are:

  1. Peel the cassava using the knife.
  2. Wash the cassava thoroughly.
  3. Grate it finely.
  4. Mix the grated cassava, grated coconut, and a teaspoon of salt well.
  5. Make small balls with the mixture.
  6. Insert a little brown sugar into the middle of each ball.
  7. Fry them for five minutes to get delicious cemplon.
  8. When they are a light brown colour, take them out of the oil. (Make sure not to fry them any longer so that the cemplon will not be burnt)
  9. The yummy cassava balls or cemplon are ready to serve.

How to Connect a Bluetooth Speaker to Android Smartphone

1. Ensure that you must disconnect other voice or stereo Bluetooth connection before connecting your Bluetooth speaker to the smart phone. It cannot be used at the same time.

2. Activate the Bluetooth speaker by pressing the Switch On or Power button on the Speaker’s body.

3. Activate the Bluetooth connection on your smartphone.

4. Connect the Bluetooth speaker to the smartphone. A list of available devices will appear (most wireless speakers let you connect a number of devices including laptops and tablets at the same time) on the Bluetooth menuFind the name of your Bluetooth speaker. Then tap it. Test the Bluetooth speaker’s sound.

5. Play music or video on your smartphone. Then, set the volume to test the sound. If it doesn’t work, redo from the first steps. Just make sure your speaker is on and your Bluetooth connection is also on
